#### IV.

Thou livest, but not from any restricted season nor from any known
period.  
Thou livest, but not through breath and soul, for Thou art soul of the
soul.  
Thou livest, but not with the life of man, which is like unto vanity and
its end the moth and the worm.  
Thou livest, and he who layeth hold of Thy secret shall find eternal
delight:  
"He shall eat and live for ever."

